column5: Lloyd is looking for up to 4 people to go fishing with him this saturday on bay of quinte  I would like to go , if anyone one would like to stop and pick me up on the way there, I would love to go.. I live in Bradford  even if I can't find someone in this area going, someone should jump on this great fishing trip
and here I thought you were talking about Mariko!
if it gets me someone to drive me down there, I will lie and say she is coming well maybe not coming but ....never mind..LOL
Now I know what you do when the little women is on afternoons. You sell charter rides.Any good money in that?

don't know, I only pay for my share of gas  I have never made anything  but I guess it could be a source of income if you knew enough guides  doesn't look like you want to give up a day of hunting to get a bunch of walleye
I would be all over it if I didn't need to close the cottage this weekend
it's not the best weekend with thanksgiving and all but the weather...wow

I cant be bothered reeling fish after fish in,when I can be in a stand and have a nice undisturbed day.  The weather looks like morning sits at best. I,ll be on the river in the AM friday,then hang,n out like a monkey the rest of the weekend.Wonder if the banana theory is the same for hunting?
Supposed to be 28C on Saturday lads.... someone get on it !
I'm in the Markham area. I'll carpool if anyone else can make it happen.
Ok so do we have anyone 100% in?
